1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with improving the recognition rate of CNNs in the presence of noise, which is a common problem in computer vision applications. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a novel method of adjusting the biases of neurons in the convolutional layers, which is a machine learning technique. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with improving the performance of AI systems in noisy environments. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper deals with adjusting the biases of neurons in CNNs, which is a neural computing technique. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with improving the recognition rate of CNNs in noisy environments, which is relevant to multimedia applications such as image and video processing.
